非商业性互惠公共许可（NCRPL v1.1）​​
零、语言优先性​
 - 本协议中文版本为原始版本，英文版本为翻译版本。
 - 若中英文版本存在语义差异，​以中文版条款为准，英文版本仅作参考。
 - 任何第三方对协议的引用或解释，均需以中文版内容为最终依据。
​一、定义​
​ - 本协议​：指《非商业性互惠公共许可》v1.1。
​ - 原始作品​：依据本协议发布的源代码、文档、设计或其他原创内容（明确包含数据、算法及接口设计）。
​ - 衍生作品​：对原始作品进行修改、翻译、重组、与其他内容结合，​或通过动态链接、服务调用等方式依赖原始作品核心功能形成的作品。
​ - 商业化使用：
 - 销售、租赁、订阅原始作品或衍生作品；
 - 将作品集成至付费产品或服务（包括SaaS、API服务等间接获利形式）；
 - 通过广告、用户数据货币化（如收集用户数据用于定向广告或第三方交易）、募资等获利；
​ - 例外​：非营利组织筹款。
​贡献者​：原始作品的版权持有人及后续经其授权的衍生作品修改者。
​二、授予的权利​
​ - 非独占、全球性许可​：
 - 允许免费使用、复制、分发原始作品及衍生作品。
​ - 修改与创作衍生作品​：
 - 允许修改原始作品并创建衍生作品，​但必须遵守第三部分的分发要求。
​ - 专利授权：
    - 贡献者授予用户不可撤销的、免版税专利许可，覆盖其贡献部分相关专利，​仅限非商业化使用。
​三、分发要求​
​ - 源代码义务​：
    - 分发原始作品或衍生作品时，必须提供完整、可编译的源代码​（包括构建脚本及依赖说明）。
​ - 协议一致性​：
    - 衍生作品必须采用与本协议完全相同的条款发布（禁止附加额外限制或闭源例外）。
 - ​署名要求​：
    - 所有副本及衍生作品需显著保留原始版权声明、许可声明、免责条款及修改记录（新增修改者署名）。
​四、限制​
​- 禁止商业化​：
    - 任何商业化使用需额外获得贡献者书面授权。
​ - 禁止技术规避​：
    - 不得通过拆分服务、中间层封装、云服务接口等技术手段绕过非商业限制。
 - ​兼容性限制​：
  - 因条款限制，​本协议与GPL/AGPL等Copyleft协议不兼容，且不得与其他许可证混合使用。
​五、免责声明与责任限制​
 - ​无担保​：
  - 作品按“现状”提供，贡献者不对适用性、安全性、准确性作担保。
 - ​责任范围​：
    - 贡献者不承担任何直接、间接、偶然、特殊或后果性损害​（包括数据损失、商誉损害等）。
 - ​第三方风险：
    - 若原始作品包含第三方代码，用户需自行承担合规风险，贡献者不提供连带担保。
​六、协议终止​
​ - 自动终止​：
    - 违反协议（如商业化、闭源分发）时，权利自动终止，需立即停止使用并销毁副本。
 - ​恢复：
    - 首次违规者可在30天内纠正行为并书面承诺合规后恢复权利（仅限一次机会）。
​七、其他条款​
 - ​协议升级​：
    - 贡献者有权发布新版本协议，用户可选择遵循NCRPL v1.1或后续版本​（但衍生作品需同步升级）。
- ​法律管辖​：
    - 本协议受版权法及贡献者所在地法律管辖，争议应通过仲裁解决​（排除集体诉讼）。
 - ​分离性原则​：
    - 若部分条款无效，​其余条款仍具有法律效力。


Non-Commercial Reciprocal Public License (NCRPL v1.1)  

​Section 0: Language Priority​
• This Agreement is originally published in Chinese, and the English version is a translation.
​• In case of discrepancies between the Chinese and English versions, the Chinese version shall prevail​ and serve as the definitive interpretation of this Agreement.
• Third-party references or explanations of this Agreement must prioritize the Chinese version as the authoritative source.

I. Definitions

• This Agreement: Refers to the Non-Commercial Reciprocal Public License version 1.1.  

• Original Work: Source code, documentation, design, or other original content published under this Agreement (explicitly including data, algorithms, and interface designs).  

• Derivative Works: Works created by modifying, translating, reorganizing, integrating with other content, or forming through dynamic linking, service invocation, or other means that depend on the core functionality of the Original Work.  

• Commercial Use (further clarified):  

  • Selling, leasing, or subscribing to the Original Work or Derivative Works;  

  • Integrating the Work into paid products or services (including indirect revenue models such as SaaS, API services);  

  • Generating profits through advertising, user data monetization (e.g., collecting user data for targeted advertising or third-party transactions), or fundraising;  

  • Exception: Fundraising by non-profit organizations.  

• Contributor: The copyright holder of the Original Work and subsequent modifiers authorized by the Contributor.  

II. Granted Rights

• Non-Exclusive, Worldwide License:  

  • Allows free use, reproduction, and distribution of the Original Work and Derivative Works.  

• Modification and Creation of Derivative Works:  

  • Permits modification of the Original Work and creation of Derivative Works, provided compliance with the distribution requirements in Section III.  

• Patent Grant (newly added):  

  • Contributors grant users an irrevocable, royalty-free patent license covering patents related to their contributions, limited to non-commercial use.  

III. Distribution Requirements

• Source Code Obligation:  

  • When distributing the Original Work or Derivative Works, complete and compilable source code (including build scripts and dependency instructions) must be provided.  

• Protocol Consistency:  

  • Derivative Works must be published under terms identical to this Agreement (additional restrictions or closed-source exceptions are prohibited).  

• Attribution Requirement:  

  • All copies and Derivative Works must retain, in a prominent manner, the original copyright notice, license notice, disclaimer of warranties, modification records, and new modifier attributions.  

IV. Limitations

• Prohibition of Commercial Use:  

  • Any commercial use requires additional written authorization from the Contributor (e.g., a dual-track commercial license system).  

• Prohibition of Technical Circumvention:  

  • No acts of technical circumvention (e.g., service splitting, middleware encapsulation, cloud service interfaces) to bypass non-commercial restrictions are permitted.  

• Compatibility Restriction:  

  • This Agreement is incompatible with Copyleft licenses such as GPL/AGPL and must not be combined with other licenses.  

V. Disclaimer of Warranties and Limitation of Liability

• No Warranty:  

  • The Work is provided "as is," and Contributors make no representations or warranties regarding its applicability, security, or accuracy.  

• Limitation of Liability:  

  • Contributors shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages (including data loss, goodwill damage, etc.).  

• Third-Party Risks:  

  • If the Original Work includes third-party code, users assume sole responsibility for compliance with applicable laws; Contributors shall not bear joint and several liability.  

VI. Termination of the Agreement

• Automatic Termination:  

  • In the event of a breach (e.g., commercial use, closed-source distribution), the rights granted under this Agreement automatically terminate. Users must immediately cease use and destroy all copies.  

• Restoration:  

  • First-time violators may restore rights within 30 days by correcting the breach and providing written confirmation of compliance (limited to one opportunity).  

VII. Miscellaneous Provisions

• Protocol Upgrades:  

  • Contributors may publish new versions of the Agreement. Users may choose to comply with NCRPL v1.1 or subsequent versions, but Derivative Works must be upgraded accordingly.  

• Governing Law:  

  • This Agreement is governed by copyright law and the laws of the Contributor’s jurisdiction. Disputes shall be resolved through arbitration (excluding class litigation).  

• Severability:  

  • If any provision is invalid, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.